## Design Notes

| Area | Decision |
|---|---|
| **Reference implementation** | `_InMemoryPatientSearchService` keeps the test file runnable in CI before the real module exists. Replace with real imports once available. |
| **Scoping** | Every happy-path assertion explicitly checks `assigned_clinician_id` so accidental cross-clinician leakage is always caught. |
| **Permission denial** | Covers `None` caller, wrong role, expired session, deactivated account, and missing `clinician_id` key. |
| **Missing mandatory elements** | Empty string, whitespace-only, `None`, wrong type, impossible date, below-minimum length, and injection strings. |
| **Conflicting state** | MRN + other criteria, maintenance mode, record-lock, concurrent transfer, and duplicate MRN integrity violation. |
| **Audit** | Patching `_emit_audit_event` asserts logging is invoked for both success and failure paths. |
| **Pagination & shape** | Rounded out to cover real-world API behaviour without being over-specified. |
